Don't Die

by: Kevin Xu

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I decided to make this game because I have played and created this type of game before. While playing it, I felt it was pretty fun to play as well, and also pretty easy to make. Also, I didn't want to have a game that is the same as what is already out that everybody could play. For those reasons, I made this game over all the other games I could have made.

2. What I Learned

From user testing, few issues arose, such as obstacles flashing, and keybindings not working. After all of the problems are fixed, the feedback on the game were all pretty good.

3. Architecture of My Game

In the game, the character, which is a spaceship landing, are trying to escape the space junk left in the sky. Once the spaceship hits any space junk, it break and the astronaut will die. The architecture of the game is using JFrames and JPanels to create the window, with the Graphics method to draw the images and the colors.

4. Technical Implementation

During the main game class, it had two different images as obstacles. I am most proud of that because it took a long time to make figure out, as it had issues without a few things. I first started trying to get keybinds to work. However, they do not work as the character movement required updating the keys, which some input methods don't support. After I gave up on keybinds, I started working on the game, until the end where the two obstacles would not work. In the end, the obstacles are fixed, and a new game is born.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part of this project is the keybinds and obstacles. For the keybinds, the problem resides in the operating system, as some input methods keep inputting the key, whiles some only inputs it once. The ones that input it only once does not work with the game, so I gave up on the idea of having a keybind. When I tried to add two different images for the obstacles, the images flashed back and forth on all the obstacles. To fix that problem, I added another class just for the second image and had two different obstacles and spawners.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

In the future, I would like to have the keybinds working. If I were to continue, I would probably add more visual appeal to the game, including more types of obstacles.
